messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full request path
- /v1/book

All methods allowed
- False

Supported methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: False
- POST: True
- OPTIONS: False
- TRACE: False
- GET: True
- PUT: False
- DELETE: False
- PATCH: False

Explanation
- Blueprints and prefixes:
  - create_v1() registers the book blueprint with url_prefix="/book".
  - create_v1() itself is registered in the application with url_prefix="/v1".
  - Those combine to form the full prefix /v1/book. The route in question uses the empty route string "" on book_api, so the full path is /v1/book.
- Routes mapped to this path in app/api/v1/book.py:
  - get_books is decorated with @book_api.route("") and implements the listing; it is the GET handler for /v1/book.
  - create_book is decorated with @book_api.route("", methods=["POST"]) and implements POST /v1/book.
- Method decisions:
  - POST is explicitly declared on create_book, so POST = True.
  - GET is the handler implemented by get_books (route decorator without explicit methods implies a GET handler in this code), so GET = True.
  - HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH are not explicitly declared on the "" route in the source, therefore they are reported as False (the result is based on what the code explicitly shows).
